snippet.textDisplay:
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "This movie is garbage" phone rings "Hello?"
EA: "Well we know how to make it better"
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "I thought I blocked your number"
EA: "I know, I know, but I'm different now, and I have a really cool idea."
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "Well okay, since you still have the license for the Star Wars genre and because you stuck the name of one of the most beloved Star Wars video games that nearly defined my childhood, I'll hear it."
EA: "You get to PLAY the movie, so instead of a boring, unimaginative movie with great special effects and less substance and flavor than a stale turnip, you get to play a super exciting new video game with all the characters you've come to love in the new trilogy!
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "But...you guys already made that. Well, okay okay, is it going to introduce any new, imaginative stories, like perhaps exploring what happened in the thirty years prior to The Force Awakens?"
EA: "Well...no. But thats because you don't get to see Rey and Finn and Kylo in that time, and I know that everyone wants to play as them, not Luke or Han Solo. Trust me, we did our research."
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "Okay...well I know this will probably some sort of free DLC, since I got an incredibly short single player campaign in the actual game that was not ambitious at all with the story that it tells, right?"
EA: "Well not quite."
Loyal Star Wars Fans: "Well then what is it?"
EA: "Weeeeeeelll, I was going to do all that but then it turned that was really hard. But, I know you're upset, but, and stay with me, you can get RED stormtroopers!!! And, and Kylo can get RED cracks in his helmet!!! How great is that?!?!"
Loyal Star Wars Fans: sighs

snippet.textDisplay:
REY


REY SKYWALKER!




I delighted the 2017 edition because of the fact we were allowed to play as Rey! However, you guys and gals simply kept the fighting bizarre and incomplete which made me quit despite the ability to enjoy Rey.


The mere reasons i got to quit the game were listed on the following;


1) Each hero was granted different abilities. At first glance this move looked somewhat reasonable but not being able to use the Force Push, Pull as Rey definitely discouraged me afterwards.


2) The usage of the Force and the lightsaber moves including the flips were found near nowhere in your game. While the blocking using the lightsaber felt awesome, the fighting mechanics never allowed us to feel the battles mostly due to not being capable of experimenting any lightsaber collisions or lightsaber vs any weapon used similar to it such as staff. Fights happened like Rey hits with her lightsaber and then the rival hit theirs , non hits each other's weapons turning out pretty lame and tasteless adding the awkward use of the Force powers.


If you ever bring some lightsaber vs any similar weapon collisions, make Force Jump and other kinds of Force more reasonable, usable by any saber wielding hero, your game could feel fascinating as much as Star Wars Jedi Fallen Order!





RETURNING TO THE MOVIE!




I saw the movie in theatre this afternoon. It was terrific! (As İ ever knew this movie would be fascinating that i stayed away from all the trailers and teasers before watching the movie)


Whomever badmouthing regarding the new trilogy are either obsessed with Darth Vader , lightsaber battles or hate the power of a girl. There is truly no other explanation for such people.


I do not consider myself a true fan of Star Wars series but i watched entire series and Rey character has definitely taken Star Wars onto a fantastic level.


I have always been an admirer of Obi Wan even though i knew hes a bit cocky or Padmé Amidala - "The Naboo Queen" more than anything and anybody else entire series until i saw Rey in the Star Wars :The Force Awakens.


Since that moment, i have fancied Rey due to her being a Jedi, her beautifully made lovely hair, her accent, her resistance against the Dark Side and many stuff. That character has happened to be my sole reason to experience Star Wars Battlefront 2 (2017) game. Playing as her in the game was brilliant.


SPOILER COMES


SPOILER


SPOILER




SPOILER




HUGE SPOILER



Anyways, i saw the movie and what i anticipated occurred.


The audience was fooled that Rey will turn into dark side. however, the opposite happened! Kylo turned Ben and he helped her fell Palpatine.


But how could such thing happen how could that be even possible?


When Kylo Ren and Rey was dueling each other under the storm, Rey felt pretty vulnerable and Kylo overcame her. However, Princess Leia appeared all of a sudden and contacted Ben through the Force.(not through cellphones though) Ben is her son, u know. As soon as Kylo Ren lifted his crimson lightsaber to murder Rey, Leia stopped her and tried to pulled him into the Light. Kylo ceased. At the moment, Leia died cos Leia gave her Force Energy or lets say Life Energy to Ben. His anger was fading slowly and then Han Solo(his father) appeared and talked to Ben. Then, Kylo half dropped his weapon, Rey captured his lightsaber and staggered Ben. Not a long time later, Rey began crying. As she noticed its not late yet, gave her hand to Kylo's wound and used Force Heal to bring back Ben to life. After that, Kylo totally turned Ben and threw his crimson lightsaber into the sea.


NOTE :Before this encounter, Rey sought to find a Sith Wayfinder to locate Palpatine and inside a place, she faced HER DARKSIDE! That Dark Rey was handling a double bladed crimson lightsaber and put on a black robe. Her face also was withered like all the Dark Side members.(Though its interesting that Kylo's face has never been like that. It was always human.) Then, Rey and her dark equivalent fought a bit. Dark counterpart attempted to lure her trying to persuade her to become a Sith as it lies in her veins. implying that Rey is attached to Palpatine by blood.


At that time, Rey moved to a different place to seek Palpatine. As soon as she faced Palpatine, the conversation commenced. Palpatine attempted to pull her into the dark side to claim her as a Sith Empress. (As soon as she kills the Emperor a.k.a. Palpatine and take the throne of him to rule all the galaxy). During that, Emperor was spreading all his tremendous Force Lightning across the space and devour all the Resistance Forces including Finn, Poe, Chewie, Lando Calrissian and others. Palpatine was showcasing Rey that destruction in order to convince her and to make her to be embraced by the Dark Side. Rey appeared to be convinced and walked towards the Emperor, it turned out that though she fooled him. Short time after, she concealed her hands in her back and then cloned her lightsaber for Ben arriving to find and rescue Rey to use against the Sith he faces as Ben had dumped his saber before. Then, Ben showed up before Emperor and two attempted to fight the Emperor. Emperor ruined them both sending all his immense Force Lightning and rendered them useless, disabled both of them. The Emperor cast the Force Push against Ben and threw him away. Simultaneously, he was devouring entire Resistance fleet across the galaxy, spreading his massive Lightning. But, it was not finished. While downed, Rey opened her eyes and called them to side her, first inactivating the Force Lightning and secondly reflecting it against the Emperor. As the Emperor disrupted her and absorbed her energy, Rey was rendered unconscious while the Emperor was annihilated due to his power reflected against him. Short time later, The Resistance Forces led by Finn, Poe, Chewie and Lando turned the tide as Rey helped them to do resulting in the wipe of the Star Destroyers one by one. However, Rey was about to die. Ben achieved to return and found Rey unconscious.
Grabbed her and made his Force Energy flow through her (paying his debt to Rey) allowing to revive her while sacrificing his own life. Before Ben died, both stared at each other and then Ben passed away.


After putting and end to Emperor, Rey returned to where Princess Leia commands the Resistance from. She learned Leia died (perhaps i am confusing this part)


Poe, Finn and Rey hugged. Then Rey moved to Tatooine and buried the sabers of Luke and Leia. (blue and green). -Actually, two were known to be mainly equipped by Luke Skywalker though the movie shows that Leia trained Luke with the green one while Luke handles the blue -


After burying two sabers. She watches the binary sunset and then while she is about to leave there, an old woman asks her who she is. She reveals her first name however, the woman persists in asks again "Rey who?" . Then Luke and Leia shows up and
she says Rey Skywalker!


-----------------------


LITTLE SPOILER


There are many other scenes such as Kylo tries to lure her at the beginning of the movie, tracks her. Rey and her buddies tries to escape. In a moment, Chewie is captured and taken to a Star Destroyer. Before that, Rey uses the Force Lightning and tears the ship apart while trying to save Chewie. Thinks Chewie is dead because of her. But then she is informed that Chewie was taken with another ship. Rey faces Kylo's illusions and many times and fights him, in one of them smashes Vader's mask.


Finn meets a girl who was once a stormtrooper like him and she joins The Resistance. Poe gets struck on with a girl called Zorii who once fought for the First Order who helps them by the threat of Rey. Poe wanna kiss her, she rejects but she lets them to gain access to a Star Destroyer with her old medal.

LITTLE SPOILER


All in all, i loved the movie. Rey is the finest hero for me!
